# ==============================================================================
# Environment Variables - Local Development
# ==============================================================================
# Copy this file to .dev.vars and fill in your actual values
# .dev.vars is gitignored and will NOT be committed to the repository
# ==============================================================================

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Session Secret (REQUIRED)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Generate a secure random string (minimum 32 characters)
# You can generate one with: openssl rand -hex 32
SESSION_SECRET=your_session_secret_here_min_32_chars_use_openssl_rand_hex_32

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GitHub OAuth (Optional)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# To enable GitHub OAuth:
# 1. Go to https://github.com/settings/developers
# 2. Click "New OAuth App"
# 3. Application name: Your app name
# 4. Homepage URL: http://localhost:3000
# 5. Authorization callback URL: http://localhost:3000/oauth/github/callback
# 6. Copy the Client ID and generate a Client Secret
# 7. Uncomment and fill in the values below:

# GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_github_client_id_here
# GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=your_github_client_secret_here

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google OAuth (Optional)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# To enable Google OAuth:
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# 2. Create a new project or select an existing one
# 3. Click "Create Credentials" â†’ "OAuth client ID"
# 4. Application type: Web application
# 5. Authorized JavaScript origins: http://localhost:3000
# 6. Authorized redirect URIs: http://localhost:3000/oauth/google/callback
# 7. Copy the Client ID and Client Secret
# 8. Uncomment and fill in the values below:

# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id_here
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_google_client_secret_here

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Auth0 OAuth (Optional)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# To enable Auth0 OAuth:
# 1. Go to https://manage.auth0.com/dashboard
# 2. Create a new application or select an existing one
# 3. Application type: Regular Web Application
# 4. Allowed Callback URLs: http://localhost:3000/oauth/auth0/callback
# 5. Allowed Logout URLs: http://localhost:3000
# 6. Copy the Domain, Client ID, and Client Secret
# 7. Uncomment and fill in the values below:

# AUTH0_DOMAIN=your-tenant.auth0.com
# AUTH0_CLIENT_ID=your_auth0_client_id_here
# AUTH0_CLIENT_SECRET=your_auth0_client_secret_here

# ==============================================================================
# Production Deployment
# ==============================================================================
# For production, set these as secrets using Wrangler:
#
# Session secret:
#   wrangler secret put SESSION_SECRET --env production
#
# GitHub OAuth:
#   wrangler secret put GITHUB_CLIENT_ID --env production
#   wrangler secret put GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET --env production
#
# Google OAuth:
#   wrangler secret put GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID --env production
#   wrangler secret put GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET --env production
#
# Auth0 OAuth:
#   wrangler secret put AUTH0_DOMAIN --env production
#   wrangler secret put AUTH0_CLIENT_ID --env production
#   wrangler secret put AUTH0_CLIENT_SECRET --env production
#
# IMPORTANT: Update OAuth callback URLs in provider settings to use your
# production domain (e.g., https://yourdomain.com/oauth/{provider}/callback)
# ==============================================================================
